{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17492929","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17492929"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T06:50:46+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T06:50:46+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"1188"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"1188","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/1188"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.15,0.05,0.25,0.43,0.12]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"1188"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"53471"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"1188","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/1188"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"1188"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"38940"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"5"},{"type":"tags","id":"19"},{"type":"tags","id":"24"},{"type":"tags","id":"30"},{"type":"tags","id":"64"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"498"},{"type":"tags","id":"934"},{"type":"tags","id":"1109"},{"type":"tags","id":"4159"},{"type":"tags","id":"4578"},{"type":"tags","id":"5771"},{"type":"tags","id":"9097"},{"type":"tags","id":"9103"},{"type":"tags","id":"9598"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"261"},{"type":"contributions","id":"15802"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"53471","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/53471"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 76-year-old woman presents with a two day history of generalised, colicky abdominal pain distension and constipation. Her medical history includes Parkinson\u0027s disease, hypertension, diabetes and an appendicectomy at the age of 17. She takes levodopa, perindopril, aspirin and metformin. On examination her abdomen is distended and soft with increased bowel sounds. There are no groin swellings. Rectal examination is normal. A plain abdominal X-ray is performed (Image).\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most likely underlying cause of her current problem?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Gallstone ileus","Carcinoma of the caecum","Pseudo-obstruction","Adhesions","Paralytic ileus"],"correctOptions":[3],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe X-ray shows dilated loops of small bowel, recognised by their central distribution and the valvulae conniventes (plicae circulares or small bowel mucosal folds) running across the lumen - see arrow (Image). Pseudo-obstruction usually involves the large bowel and there is usually a well-defined event (eg spinal surgery) that precedes the obstruction. A paralytic ileus is unlikely since this tends to be associated with diminished bowel sounds. The other three options might all explain the obstruction and the commonest of these is \u003Cstrong\u003Eadhesions\u003C/strong\u003E. Appendicectomy is the commonest cause of adhesive-obstruction and the operation itself is often decades earlier than the episode of intestinal obstruction.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EGallstone ileus will classically have biliary gas visible over the liver on X-ray due to fistula formation between the biliary system and intestine. Occasionally the calcified gallstone will be seen in the intestine as a transition point. Neither are seen here.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Adhesions are the commonest cause of small bowel obstruction in the developed world"],"references":["Mullan CP, Siewert B, Eisenberg RL. Small Bowel Obstruction. AJR 2012; 198:W105-17. Available at: https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/22268199/"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"38940"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"1188"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[{"type":"media","id":"15318"}]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[{"type":"media","id":"20367"}]}}},{"type":"media","id":"15318","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/media/15318"},"attributes":{"mimeType":"image/jpeg","url":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/4b642bf7-71d0-4bb4-aaa3-d36366b9d294.jpg","thumbUrl":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/4b642bf7-71d0-4bb4-aaa3-d36366b9d294.jpg","isProcessed":true,"width":490,"height":600}},{"type":"media","id":"20367","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/media/20367"},"attributes":{"mimeType":"image/jpeg","url":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/ysoR0roGTK2DWN7eDgZgrRQHl3umGn.jpg","thumbUrl":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/ysoR0roGTK2DWN7eDgZgrRQHl3umGn.jpg","isProcessed":true,"width":490,"height":600}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"38940","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/38940"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-09-21T21:15:13+09:30","updatedAt":"2024-09-21T21:16:01+09:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"1188"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"53471"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"5","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/5"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\udd2d","name":"Gastroenterology","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2024-11-21T09:49:43+10:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"1"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"19","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/19"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\udd2a","name":"General Surgery","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2024-11-21T09:47:20+10:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"2"}}